<p class="">    <h1>Key Challenges in the CG Visual Service Market</h1>    <ul>        <li><strong>High Production Costs:</strong> The cost of creating high-quality CG visuals can be prohibitively high, particularly for smaller studios. This includes expenses related to software licenses, skilled labor, and advanced hardware.</li>        <li><strong>Talent Shortage:</strong> There is a significant demand for skilled professionals in the CG sector, but a shortage of experienced artists and technicians makes it challenging for companies to scale their operations efficiently.</li>        <li><strong>Rapid Technological Advancements:</strong> Keeping pace with rapidly evolving technology poses a challenge for many firms. The constant need for investment in training and tools can strain budgets and resources.</li>        <li><strong>Intellectual Property Issues:</strong> As CG visuals often incorporate elements from various sources, companies must navigate complex intellectual property laws, which can lead to legal challenges and increased costs for licensing.</li>        <li><strong>Competitive Landscape:</strong> The CG visual service market is becoming increasingly crowded, leading to intense competition. Companies often struggle to differentiate themselves and secure clients.</li>    </ul>    <h2>Potential Growth Opportunities</h2>    <ul>        <li><strong>Integration of AI and Machine Learning:</strong> The adoption of AI technologies can streamline production processes, improve data analysis, and enhance creative workflows, providing companies with a significant competitive advantage.</li>        <li><strong>Expansion of Virtual and Augmented Reality:</strong> The growing demand for immersive experiences in industries such as gaming, healthcare, and education creates substantial opportunities for CG services focused on VR and AR applications.</li>        <li><strong>Cross-Industry Collaborations:</strong> Collaborating with sectors like marketing, gaming, and fil